Support




























Corporate Citizenship





LRAD Corporation and its employees are making a difference by dedicating time, resources and equipment to save and make lives better.
 
 The Elizabeth Taylor Aids Foundation
The Company donated four LRAD 100X systems to The Elizabeth Taylor AIDS Foundation (“ETAF”) in July 2016 for use on its mobile health clinics in Malawi. The communication systems are being utilized to broadcast greetings, clinic services and health education information to rural villagers in the Mulanje and Phalombe districts.
“Through our implementing partner, the Global AIDS Interfaith Alliance (“GAIA”), our mobile health care clinics have provided life-sustaining health care to the 1 million residents in these districts for almost a decade,” stated ETAF Managing Director, Joel Goldman. “LRAD Corporation’s generous donation equips our mobile clinics with versatile public address systems to better reach the communities we serve in Malawi.” For more information about the LRAD 100X and its use by GAIA/ETAF, please click Humanitarian Communication
 Ride Across America
Retired Marine Sgt. Toran Gaal’s June – August 2015 Ride Across America benefited the Semper Fi Fund. Ret. Sgt. Gaal lost both his legs, above his knee and hip, and suffered a brain injury in an IED explosion June 2011, in Afghanistan.
His continuing mission is to raise awareness and educate people on the lives of those who are wounded and injured while serving in the U.S. military.  Read more about Ret. Sgt. Gaal and his 3,800-mile Ride Across America:
http://www.torangaal.com. For more information on the Semper Fi Fund, visit: https://semperfifund.org

 Domestic Incidents
During and after events such as Hurricane Katrina, the landslides in Oso WA, and flooding in Boulder CO  – the Company responded by lending LRAD systems to law enforcement and the National Guard to communicate rescue instructions to stranded survivors and to provide information on relief and humanitarian assistance to people on the ground.
Read the Colorado National Guard ‘Thank You’ letter >>

 Polinsky Children’s Center (PCC)
The A.B. and Jessie Polinsky Children’s Center (PCC) is the emergency shelter for children in San Diego County. PCC provides services to children who have been physically, sexually, and or emotionally abused, medically or physically neglected, and/or have no parent or guardian. The Company and its employees participate generously in the annual toy drive to benefit PCC and children in need. For more information visit: http://promises2kids.org

 Holes for Heroes® 
Holes for Heroes presents Military Appreciation events for the purpose of saluting, thanking and supporting wounded and recovering military heroes, front-lined based troops, children and families of deployed troops and KIAs and recovering veterans.
In 2013, the Company’s sponsorship at the Holes for Heroes annual golf tournament served as a catalyst for a donation and future assistance to the Support the Enlisted Project (STEP). STEP provides emergency financial and transition assistance grants to active duty and recently discharged enlisted military members and their families. For more information visit: http://www.stepsocal.org



